Objective: Learn the basics of CSS by applying styles to an HTML structure.

Guidelines:
Use the provided HTML structure and add the CSS.
Style the webpage according to the following requirements:
Change background colors.
Adjust font sizes and colours.
Add spacing and borders.
Centre content.
HTML Structure of Code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>Delicious Apple Pie Recipe</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #fffbea;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }


        #hero {
            background-image: url('https://i.imgur.com/oXrLmSl.jpg&#39;);
            /* Add your image path */
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            height: 400px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            text-align: center;
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Grandma's Secret Apple Pie</h1>
    </header>
     <section id="hero">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h2>Welcome to Our Business</h2>
